## Requirements
- Git
- CMake (version 3.10 or higher)
- C++ compiler (e.g., GCC or Clang)

## Clone the Repository
Clone the repository to your local machine:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/game_engine.git
cd game_engine
Install Dependencies
Ubuntu/Debian
Run the following commands to install the required dependencies:

bash

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake git libglfw3 libglfw3-dev libglew-dev libglm-dev libopengl-dev
Clone the STB Image library:

bash

git clone https://github.com/nothings/stb.git ./stb
Required Libraries
You can check and download required dependencies from the following links:

GLFW
GLEW
GLM
STB Image
Run Setup Script
Make the setup script executable and run it:

bash

chmod +x setup.sh
./setup.sh

The setup script will handle any additional steps, such as downloading and setting up necessary libraries.

Build the Project
Build the project with the following steps:

bash

mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make
./GameEngine
Folder Structure
The basic folder structure of the project is as follows:

plaintext

game_engine/
├── src/
│   ├── core/
│   ├── assets/
│   ├── graphics/
│   ├── animation/
│   ├── vfx/
│   ├── ui/
│   ├── camera/
│   ├── utils/
│   ├── events/
│   ├── loading/
│   └── input/
├── assets/
│   ├── models/
│   ├── textures/
│   ├── shaders/
│   └── sounds/
├── tools/
├── bin/
├── include/
├── CMakeLists.txt


License
This project is licensed under the MIT License. See the LICENSE file for full details.

Additional Information
CMakeLists.txt: Contains the build configuration for CMake and links to required dependencies.
setup.sh: This script automatically downloads required libraries like STB Image and prepares the project for building.
Contributing
Feel free to contribute by opening issues, forking the repository, and submitting pull requests. If you encounter any problems, open an issue, and we will address it as soon as possible.

For more information on contributing, visit the GitHub repository.

Links to Required Tools
CMake
Git
GLFW
GLEW
GLM
STB Image
MIT License

Additional Setup

After cloning the repository, make sure to run the setup script to ensure all dependencies are downloaded and installed correctly.
The build folder will contain the compiled binaries once the project is built with CMake and Make.
If you are unsure or encounter any issues during the setup, you can search on YouTube for tutorial videos or use ChatGPT for clarification.

For more details about the project, refer to the individual README files inside the respective directories or visit the official repositories linked above.

Note: Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username in the links provided to ensure they point to your repository.

